<h1>Demo RailsEx</h1>

<br>
This is a demo to illustrate a use case for UDF: GitOps Automation -- using GitOps combined with data services to provide a run-time environment for applications


<br>


<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Title</th>
      <th>Summary & Link</th>
      <th colspan="3"></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>

  <tbody>
    <% @articles.each do |article| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= article.title %></td>
        <td><%= article.body %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Show', article %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_article_path(article) %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Delete', article, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' } %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>

